# User REST Client

### Get user by id (protected)
### Requires Authorization: Bearer <token>
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/{userId}
Authorization: Bearer {accesstoken}


### Example environment variables for REST client (use in your REST client extension)
### {{access_token}} - set to the JWT returned in the fragment after OAuth flow
### {{userId}} - the id of the user to fetch (e.g. from the JWT payload `userId`)

### How to extract the access_token in the browser after redirect
### The client receives the redirect to: http://localhost:3000/oauth/callback#access_token=<JWT>&...
### Use JS to read window.location.hash and extract access_token, then pass it in Authorization header for API calls.


### Successful response (200 OK)
### HTTP/1.1 200 OK
### {
###   "_id": "64f8b3a7e4a9c2b0f1d2e3c4",
###   "email": "user@example.com",
###   "role": "STUDENT",
###   "googleId": "10782345xxxxxx",
###   "createdAt": "2025-10-05T12:34:56.789Z",
###   "updatedAt": "2025-10-05T12:34:56.789Z"
### }


### Unauthorized (missing/invalid token)
### HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
### {
###   "statusCode": 401,
###   "message": "Unauthorized"
### }


### Forbidden (role mismatch / ownDataMiddleware rejected)
### HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden
### {
###   "statusCode": 403,
###   "message": "Forbidden"
### }


### Not Found
### HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found
### {
###   "statusCode": 404,
###   "message": "User not found"
### }
